Nutrition for Obese Children: No Breakfast and Cake for Dinner
More than a third of children aged 9 to 13 are overweight; while 9% of schoolchildren are overweight, 5% suffer from obesity.
According to the latest study, children suffering from obesity usually come from families leading an unhealthy lifestyle.
We once again see the importance of the environment and patterns of behavior that accompany a person for his or her healthy development.
For example, sausage appears on the tables of children suffering from obesity, almost twice as often as in families with children with a normal weight.
More than 19% of obese children ate fries for dinner on the eve of a survey related to an educational event called Obesity is not a coincidence.
Moreover, families of children suffering from obesity do not play sports.This, however, applies to most families of modern schoolchildren - only 15% of children said their parents find time to play sports at least once a week.
The study was conducted among 900 children.
The study was conducted at the end of last school year, involving almost 900 elementary schoolchildren across Bohemia.
The event Obesity is not a coincidence was held for the second consecutive year, with the support of the insurance company Všeobecná zdravotní pojišťovna and the company Unilever.
To date, more than 12 thousand pupils from 4 to 8 classes have joined the project.
Proper nutrition and adequate exercise are the main determinants of the rapidly growing number of children who suffer from either overweight or obesity.
“For example, only half of the respondents said that they eat five times a day, according to the breakfast-breakfast-lunch-breakfast-dinner scheme, but this is one of the indispensable conditions for proper nutrition,” one of the findings of the study said.
No lunch or sausage in the evening.
Experts warn that even such relative details as the constant time of family breakfast are important for healthy development.
In the Czech Republic, only 23% of school families eat breakfast together.
Most families eat breakfast separately.
The worst discovery was that in one in ten families people don’t eat breakfast at all.
Breakfast is the basis of a good daily diet.
The study found that fried food is more commonly consumed in families with children suffering from obesity.
Almost everyone – regardless of weight – drinks sweetened refrigerated drinks every day (70%).
Although more than 40% of children regularly engage in sports, this figure decreases more than twice – to 15% – when it comes to their parents.
Create your own menu.
In another part of the study, selected children (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) were asked to make their own menu based on the proposed foods and based on their tastes and preferences.
“The food preferences of Czech children aged 12-15 are far from ideal when it comes to healthy eating.”
Their favorite food includes a large number of flour, meat and sweet dishes.
“Special concern is the great popularity of sweetened refrigerated beverages,” says the final part of the study.
As the main meal, the pasta defeated the bird with a small predominance.
However, the children practically showed no interest in beans, fish and vegetable dishes.
Desire for a Healthy Lifestyle
The study also found that children are willing to change their eating habits provided they are given appropriate information.
“Many participants in the study’s control group showed a significant shift in preferences towards healthy food when they filled out a questionnaire after the end of the lecture Obesity is not a coincidence,” the project said.
This was especially noticeable, for example, in the case of sweet refrigerated drinks – more children began to prefer them to just water.
In addition, as the main meal, children were more likely to mark poultry and fish, limiting the amount of sweet dishes and baked meals.
A stylist should also be a good psychologist, say professionals
In the first article on training for stylists, I attended the volume of information on the introductory classes.
I had no idea what would happen next.
Lectures from three experts in the field; advice on choosing clothes for non-standard figures; and a workshop on how all this works in real life.
Next is more.
The closer we are to the final exam, the more information and practical tasks await us.
Training is held every Saturday and Sunday, but it is really full of information.
This time with Alenka, the director, we discussed how to dress a woman whose body is not perfectly symmetrical.
Most women are not completely symmetrical.
One has a short neck, the other has a boy's figure without proper shapes, another weighs more than normal.
A stylist should know how to visually reduce wide shoulders, extend the neck or add missing volumes.
We were given advice on how to emphasize the figure of women like Jennifer Lopez, i.e. holders of lighter breasts and hips and narrow waist, and at the same time not dress them too challengingly.
For example, if the difference in the volume of the waist and hips is so large that you can not pick up a shirt or pants, it is worth having at least one thing sewn on order.
You will definitely not regret the money invested, because perfectly seated clothes are invaluable.
In a shirt sewn on custom, you will feel much better than in one that is constantly climbing, hanging, revealing the waist, etc.
Owners of boy figures, on the other hand, can wear clothes with rushes, application, tail or folds.
Given the abundance of such information and the types of figures, I’m glad that I have a whole week to realize it all.
And yet, I’m afraid, that’s too much given the homework we got.
Each participant had to come up with two dresses for a celebrity: for the day and for the evening.
We should consider their modern appearance, their style in clothes and the type of figure.
I’m going to wear Miranda Kerr, who you may know from Victoria’s Secret advertising campaigns.
I’m happy about myself because it’s much easier to wear it than, say, Britney Spears, Christina Aguilera, who recently recovered (please keep in mind that I’m exaggerating), or the very young Selena Gomez.
We have to cut out clothes from magazines or find them on the Internet, print them out and process them with graphic programs.
Moodboard - so called the result of work - then reflects our own style and attitude to graphic image.
It is important to keep in mind the graphic component of style.
A stylist does not just dress real people, but creates product pages in magazines (based on special guidelines, such as fashion bags, coats, etc.).
This is what stylist and designer Mario Kamenich told us.
But it was only on Sunday.
Stylists need general knowledge.
The Saturday lecture, full of information on the types of figures, was revived by three guests - specialists in this field.
Stylist, Honza Pokorny; fashion designer, Yakub Polanka; and fashion photographer Ben Ranch.
Jacob reminded us that fashion is an illusion and the stylist must use this fact.
A good stylist can use one item of clothing differently.
In this case, diversity is the key to success.
For example, a trench coat can be worn in the usual way, above jeans and t-shirts, like a coat; but it can also be worn on the naked body, without clutches, like a dress.
Another option is to roll your sleeves or raise your collar, and the whole image is completely changed.
“Play with him,” he said.
Anyway, I most appreciated the following advice: “For your work, you need to know the rules perfectly.”
Then you can start breaking them,” Jacob told us.
Here I finally understood why we get all the definitions and rules, what to combine with what and why, while in fashion magazines we often see quite differently.
Not to mention fashion shows.
From Ben, a photographer, I learned that a stylist should have more options of costumes than the number of photos he needs to take.
So, for a fashion review on ten pages (equivalent to ten dresses) I must be prepared to create at least fifteen images.
Now I also know that in the picture, the object of the clothes often looks and works in combination with others at all not like in reality.
We have to keep this in mind when creating an image.
Honza Pokorna confirmed that often image and style are half of success.
Just look at Madonna, who doesn’t have a stunning vocal, but her image and marketing have turned her into a world star.
The attitude to the services of stylists in the Czech Republic is still quite cool.
Even famous people often consider this superfluous (and believe that it is enough to be an expert in something, and how they look is secondary).
And if someone finally allows us to create their style, we should expect them to call us a different (less) size than the one they actually wear.
Then we turn to Google and find out if the tabloids did not write anything about that some celebrity was fattened / lost weight, etc.
On Sunday, Honza and Mario emphasized that it was not enough for a stylist to understand fashion and be able to pick up a suit.
Our work mainly consists of communicating with the people we dress; so it’s important to be a good psychologist.
To be able to judge people, not offend them and stick to their opinion.
“If a manager asks you to look at her clothes and add a few beautiful things, you can’t throw out her entire wardrobe by telling her that her clothes are awful.”
"Find at least a few things you can praise and advise what you can wear with them," says Mario.
He also showed us exactly what a work bag should fit.
This is a bag that you tie around your waist to carry everything you need.
In addition to obvious things such as scissors, sticky rolls or English sticks, it should have a nylon thread (stylists use it when shooting certain objects, such as a bag or hat), special clips for sticking the fabric on the back in case the clothes are too large (stickers and similar items are prohibited because they spoil the clothes) or a sewing kit.
In order to get distracted from lectures and gain some practical experience, we learned how to properly make shoe pads.
Even during shooting in a studio where the floor is smooth, the helmets can get damaged – not to mention shooting outdoors.
And here we did the crawl.
You should not touch the shoes with scissors, so as not to spoil them.
This requires real skill.
I was glad that Mario praised my work.
I did not like those skills.
This is just part of what we heard during the second part of the weekend courses.
I’m beginning to realize that being a professional stylist isn’t as easy as you might say.
Need for Speed: Escape takes place in America.
Review of
What was supposed to be a careless walk turned into a routine morning trip to work due to a series of completely inappropriate and negligent mistakes.
The ambitions were satisfied to a certain extent, but it doesn’t matter because nobody obviously wanted to do the extra work.
Before the release of the new version with the subtitle "Flight" connected great hopes.
It was expected to shift the previous series of Need for Speed in a new direction; demonstration versions testified that the game would take a worthy place in the genre of racing games.
We were curious to see parts of the game where the protagonist gets out of the car and runs away.
As is often the case with NFS, the outcome is much different from what we expected.
The game is a fairly good arcade race, but the overall impression is ruined by a few unnecessary mistakes that are present in this series of games for several years.
So, in reality, this is not a mistake, but a manifestation of the inexplicable laziness of developers.
The adventure starts very well.
You become part of a story whose main character, Jack, decides to solve some personal problems by participating in an illegal race across America.
You get into a car on the west coast, in San Francisco, and your task is to get to New York first.
This idea has several interesting features.
The route consists of ten stages divided into more than fifty races.
This means that each race runs on its own route, individual stages take place in a diverse and interesting environment.
Therefore, there is no feeling that the same thing is happening all the time in the game.
Despite the fact that the graphics are at the same level as in the previous parts of the series, some tracks are pleasant to watch.
And yet the game does not cause strong emotions.
While driving a car through the desert, through the autumn suburbs or high in the snowy mountains is very pleasant.
In addition, the race occasionally revives an unusual detail.
For example, in the desert you get into a sandstorm, which significantly reduces visibility.
On the other hand, in the mountains you need to be careful not to fall under the avalanche.
The individual races are quite well arranged.
There are only a few varieties, but that is enough.
For a while you’re trying to overtake several rivals (essentially a regular race); then you’re trying to improve the time (standard secondary race); or you’re competing with one opponent.
Among other things, you occasionally encounter the police, which makes your task even more complicated.
The components on the outside of the car are new.
It’s just an interactive animation where most of the time Jack runs away from someone and you have to help him by pressing the right buttons at the right time.
Nothing complicated.
Although surprisingly, these fragments are much smaller than you might expect (only three to be precise).
In fact, it turns out to be good for the game because this property isn’t boring; considering all of the above, it’s one of the things that makes the game more fun.
The racing model follows the tracks of previous models.
This means that it is no longer something special, but it cannot be considered a disadvantage.
If you are looking for a real-life imitation, you will have to look elsewhere.
And yet this driving model is very suitable for dynamic races, although better options can be found on the market.
So far everything is very well.
However, after some time problems begin.
Unlike the driving model, the collision model is not so good.
From such a game you do not expect complicated transformations and collisions, but if you have no idea before a collision with an object, how your car will behave, something is wrong.
Usually, by overtaking or passing by cars in a dense stream, you sometimes slightly touch another car.
Or broke up.
It’s not so important because of the restart system, but it’s enough to ruin the fun.
The restarts are arranged in such a way that if you crash or get away from the track, the game brings you back to the point where it was interrupted.
However, there are only five restarts available for each race.
If you use them all, you will have to start the race from the beginning.
This is useful if something doesn’t work out, but you can’t fully rely on it.
Sometimes restarts are not enough, and you have to learn a separate section of the race.
An important disadvantage of the game is the fact that the same things often happen in the same places.
For example, some turns need to be done in a certain way, otherwise you just won’t fit.
In other cases, you encounter civilian cars in a particular location in the same configuration regardless of whether you arrive first, fifth, five seconds earlier or a minute later.
This is especially annoying in situations where you see your opponent easily passing between two cars moving in the opposite direction, whereas when you get there, the cars are already arranged so that you need to either circumvent them or lower speed.
It doesn’t matter when you find yourself next to them; everything is arranged so that the situation always happens right in front of your nose.
Competitors have other advantages.
During the game you discover several locations where, regardless of time, the same opponent outputs you in the same place.
This is especially evident at the end of the game, on a long bridge where you are driving in the opposite direction.
Obviously, your opponent has to stand up before you no matter what.
The fact is that when it runs in front of you, it makes your view worse, leading to one or more accidents on that site.
You can understand an attempt to make the game more interesting and filled with adrenaline, but this is so obvious that it quickly begins to irritate.
It’s a pity, because despite the simple driving model, the game is fun and sometimes so full of events that you don’t have time to pay attention to what’s happening around you.
It doesn’t matter what doesn’t get you bored – a concept with fifty unique tracks, a sequence of races or something else.
The idea of changing cars during races is unusual.
You need to track the gas stations along the way, as it is on them that your car can change, despite the fact that in most cases the one you already have is quite enough.
The cars are divided into three categories.
Sports cars are suitable for cities; powerful American cars – for straight sections of the highway; and exotic super sports cars for technical driving, for example, on curved mountain trails.
The main story mode is closely related to the challenge mode; it is racing on individual areas that you will learn in the course of the game.
Here you win for your personal cause both medals and points, common to the challenges and story modes.
Many options are available to get a higher level of driving: starting with cars and ending with profile data.
In addition, the profile is linked to the Autolog online feature, which, among other things, compares your results with the results of other players, and provides communication with the public.
Here’s another disadvantage, hard to understand; it’s an example from the last race in sequence.
You and your car get into the subway tunnel (we’ll think so), where you’re rushing along the rails in the dark (we’ll think so).
Your speed meter shows numbers from 150 to 200 km/h (think it is) when a subway train suddenly hits you from behind, turning your car into a pile of debris.
For several days, our editors discussed whether no one really thought a second during the creation of the game, or whether its creators really think of us as such bats.
The technical component of the game is nothing special; but the overall impression of the video game is mostly pleasant, sometimes even stunning.
Although it is a pity that at some critical moments the quality of recording, sometimes quite strongly, decreases.
This is especially true of events with a large number of participants, where a good recording would not help you too.
Sound is fine; the soundtrack is for the amateur.
In order to please the widest possible youth audience, the soundtrack has included compositions of different styles; but it is unlikely that many people will buy the game because of its music.
The overall impression of Need for Speed: Escape is quite messy.
If the game avoided obviously unnecessary mistakes, we could honestly say that Escape is the best part of NFS in the last few years.
In any case, the game leaves a feeling of incomplete.
Of course, this is good entertainment, but be prepared for the fact that the shortcomings will blind you like the airport projectors.
The choirs of Karlovy University will perform at the concert "Students in the barkhat"
For the third year in a row, Festa Academia offers to combine the International Student Day and the anniversary of the barley revolution with a musical event.
He will represent about twenty school and university choirs.
