Pride precedes defeat.
UBS officials remember the meetings of board members, where Woolfley repeated the same slogan – to move Goldman Sachs.
The Bank of America was the most powerful investment bank in the world.
At the time, he headed the "tournament table", where the successes of banks were made.
UBS wanted to get to the top of this table.
He was able to make part of that path.
UBS was the largest player in currency and government securities trading.
Authorized management consultants, however, pointed to a weak spot. By the parameter, which in banking terminology is called "stable income", UBS was far behind the largest banks.
UBS has failed in American mortgage products.
To close the hole, UBS embarked on an adventure that barely cost him his life.
In an effort to grow, the bank itself and the hedge fund it founded invested in U.S. sub-standard securities.
This developed into a large mechanism that combined securities based on American mortgages and sold them further – continuing to bear the risks itself.
Even when other banks have long been looking for a way out of this process, UBS has not stopped.
