Fujimori was hospitalized again for medical examination
Former President Alberto Fujimori was hospitalized in a state hospital on Tuesday to be examined for the loss of muscle strength observed in his legs, his family doctor said.
Fujimori, 72, who was sentenced to 25 years in prison for human rights violations committed during his reign (1990-2000), suffers from several diseases, including tongue cancer, for which he has been operated four times and is under surveillance.
