threatens to interfere in the foreign exchange market
Japanese Prime Minister Yeshiko Noda warned on Tuesday that the Japanese authorities would conduct new interventions in the foreign exchange market if the value of the yen continues to rise.
We will intervene, as we did last time, if we consider the excessive volatility of the yen exchange rate, Mr. Noda explained to the Senate.
