At the last meeting in late October, the issuer increased the purchase of Treasury bonds by 5,000 million yen (47,000 million euros), raising to 55,000,000 million yen (519,000 million euros) the ceiling of amounts it allocates to the purchase of various financial instruments to saturate the securities market.
