Paris is concerned about Islamic Maghreb’s ties to Boko Haram.
Long-presumed links between the terrorist group Al Qaeda in the Muslim Maghreb (Aqmi) and the Nigerian Boko Haram sector have been confirmed.
On Sunday, Algeria’s Deputy Foreign Minister Abdelkader Messahel even said that Algerians are now confident.
"The way these two organizations are using and the reports of the secret services show that they are actively cooperating," he explained, without going into details.
Paris appears to have come to similar conclusions.
An investigation into the kidnapping of two French men in Niger in January revealed two linkages.
