Among the debris left after the operation, French and Nigerian investigators found several phone SIM cards belonging to terrorists.
This is terror
The analysis of the calls indicated several interlocutors in Mali, Niger and Nigeria.
According to Radio France Internationale (RFI), the investigators are interested in two numbers; one points to a Nigerian who has long lived in Maidiguri, a city in northern Nigeria, the cradle of Boko Haram, and the other - a person allegedly close to Aqmi and the sect.
“This is a step forward, but we must undoubtedly wait for more reliable evidence before talking about operational cooperation between Aqmi and Boko Haram.”
“But it is possible.”
